2. Core Project Constraints & Rules

Based on past failures and infrastructure realities, our prototype must adhere to these strict guardrails:

The 5-Second Rule: Processing must take ≤5 seconds per label. The previous pilot failed because agents can 
manually review a label faster than a slow machine.

The "Mother Test" UI: Half the team is over 50. The UI must be incredibly clean, obvious, and require zero 
training.

Network Isolation: We must watch out for outbound traffic blocks. The solution should ideally run locally 
within the permitted network environment or use pre-approved Azure endpoints.

No Sensitive Data: For the prototype, we will bypass heavy FedRAMP/PII compliance by ensuring we do not upload 
or store sensitive production data.

3. High-Level Requirements Layout

Functional Requirements

Single Label Upload & Verification:

Extract text from label artwork via OCR.

Compare Brand Name and ABV against form inputs.

Fuzzy Matching Logic: Flag mismatches intelligently (e.g., "STONE'S THROW" vs "Stone's Throw" should 
pass or gently flag, not hard reject).

Strict Matching Logic: The "GOVERNMENT WARNING:" text must be exactly word-for-word, bolded, and in ALL CAPS.

Batch Upload: Ability for users to queue up multiple labels at once to handle high-volume importer dumps.

Clean Dashboard UI: Side-by-side comparison (Label Image vs. Extracted Data vs. Form Data) with clear 
green/red pass/fail indicators.

Non-Functional Requirements

Performance: Latency <5 seconds per file.

Environment: Standalone web application hosted in the existing Azure environment, avoiding any direct 
connection to the COLA legacy database.

4. Proposed Prototype Project Phase Layout

Phase 1: Discovery & Tech Spike (Weeks 1-2)
  ├── Test firewall permissions for Azure Cognitive Services / OCR endpoints.
  └── Define the exact verification logic (Fuzzy matching vs. Strict matching).

Phase 2: UI/UX Wireframing (Week 3)
  └── Create low-fidelity designs to test the "Mother Test" UI with Sarah & Dave.

Phase 3: Core Development (Weeks 4-7)
  ├── Sprint 1: OCR engine setup & Single-label verification algorithm (< 5s target).
  ├── Sprint 2: Batch upload processing queue.
  └── Sprint 3: UI frontend development and integration.

Phase 4: Testing & Pilot (Week 8)
  └── Run a limited pilot with Jenny (the champion) and Dave (the skeptic).


